---
import PortalLayout from "../layouts/PortalLayout.astro";
---

<PortalLayout title="Developers">
  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Developers</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 mb-8">Technical reference for the SMP dev team.</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <!-- Naming Conventions -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Naming Conventions</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-700 mb-3">To avoid confusion, the team uses these terms consistently:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700">
          <li><code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-bold">bethel</code> = the server (Hetzner VPS at 100.114.220.65)</li>
          <li><code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-bold">dev</code> = always the git branch (where all work happens)</li>
          <li><code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-bold">main</code> = always the production branch (triggers Netlify build)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mt-3">Example: "SSH into Bethel, push to dev, admin approves merge to main."</p>
      </section>

      <!-- SSH Access -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">SSH Access to Bethel</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Connect to the development server via Tailscale:</p>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 overflow-x-auto">
          <span>ssh bethel</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mt-3">Requires Tailscale VPN. SSH config alias is set up in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/.ssh/config</code> pointing to <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">100.114.220.65</code>. See <a href="/onboarding" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Onboarding</a> for Tailscale setup.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Developer Permissions -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Developer Permissions</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">All developers are in the <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">deploy</code> group. Each developer has their own SSH account with access to all client sites.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
          <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="font-bold text-green-800 text-sm mb-2">You CAN</p>
            <ul class="text-green-700 text-xs space-y-1">
              <li>&bull; Read and write any client site in <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">~/Sites/</code></li>
              <li>&bull; Run Claude in any site directory</li>
              <li>&bull; Run <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">npm run dev</code>, <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">npm run build</code>, git operations</li>
              <li>&bull; Use all MCP servers (Sanity, Stitch, Playwright, etc.)</li>
              <li>&bull; Use all pipeline tools on the portal</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="font-bold text-red-800 text-sm mb-2">You CANNOT</p>
            <ul class="text-red-700 text-xs space-y-1">
              <li>&bull; Edit the Tools API (<code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">/home/deploy/bin/tools-api/</code>)</li>
              <li>&bull; Edit the Portal (<code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">~/Sites/spirit-media-portal/</code>)</li>
              <li>&bull; Access secrets or .env files</li>
              <li>&bull; Restart server services (systemctl, nginx)</li>
              <li>&bull; Modify server config, firewall, or SSH settings</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-amber-800 text-sm mb-2">Permission denied?</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-xs">If you hit a permission error on a site directory, <strong>do not try to fix it yourself</strong>. Do not use sudo, change ownership, or create temp directories. Message the admin on Slack. If you have ideas for improving the tools, portal, or server setup, reach out the same way &mdash; improvements are welcome.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- MCP Servers -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">MCP Servers</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Every site directory on Bethel has a <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">.mcp.json</code> symlinked from <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">/home/deploy/.mcp.json</code>. This gives Claude Code access to all integrations automatically.</p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-200">
                <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-stone-500 font-semibold">Server</th>
                <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-stone-500 font-semibold">Service</th>
                <th class="text-left py-2 text-stone-500 font-semibold">Purpose</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-stone-700">
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Stitch</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Google Stitch 2.0</td><td class="py-2">AI design &mdash; page designs and design systems</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Sanity</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">mcp.sanity.io</td><td class="py-2">Content management and image assets</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Netlify</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">@netlify/mcp</td><td class="py-2">Hosting, deploys, build status</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Cloudflare</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">@cloudflare/mcp-server-cloudflare</td><td class="py-2">DNS, SSL, CDN, R2 storage</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Playwright</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">@anthropic/mcp-playwright</td><td class="py-2">Browser screenshots and testing</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">GHL</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">services.leadconnectorhq.com</td><td class="py-2">CRM, forms, contacts, marketing</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Google Docs</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">@a-bonus/google-docs-mcp</td><td class="py-2">Documents and content drafts</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Security -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Security</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700 text-sm">
          <li>&bull; Never commit passwords or API keys to Git</li>
          <li>&bull; All secrets are stored in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/.secrets</code> (chmod 600) &mdash; accessible only by the deploy account</li>
          <li>&bull; Claude uses OAuth (no API key) &mdash; authenticated via Claude Team subscription</li>
          <li>&bull; Credentials are in Bitwarden Vault &mdash; ask admin for access</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Session Best Practices -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Session Best Practices</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mb-2">Start every session from the site directory:</p>
            <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-4 py-3 font-mono text-sm text-stone-700">cd ~/Sites/&lt;slug&gt; && claude</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mb-2">For migrations, say:</p>
            <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-4 py-3 text-sm italic text-stone-700">"continue migration"</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mb-2">For new site builds, say:</p>
            <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-4 py-3 text-sm italic text-stone-700">"continue newsite"</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mb-2">At the end of every session:</p>
            <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-4 py-3 text-sm italic text-stone-700">"Update CLAUDE.md with what we did today"</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-3">Claude reads the site's CLAUDE.md and the protocol automatically. It knows which phase you're on and what to do next.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- GitHub SSH Key Setup -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">GitHub SSH Key Setup</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Generate an SSH key and add it to your GitHub account so you can push/pull without entering passwords.</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1">Step 1 &mdash; Generate a key</p>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 overflow-x-auto">
              <span>ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your@email.com"</span>
              <button class="copy-btn px-3 py-1 bg-red-50 hover:bg-red-100 text-red-700 rounded text-xs font-semibold ml-4 font-sans" data-copy='ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your@email.com"'>Copy</button>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1">Step 2 &mdash; Copy the public key</p>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 overflow-x-auto">
              <span>cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub</span>
              <button class="copy-btn px-3 py-1 bg-red-50 hover:bg-red-100 text-red-700 rounded text-xs font-semibold ml-4 font-sans" data-copy="cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub">Copy</button>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1">Step 3 &mdash; Add to GitHub</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Go to <a href="https://github.com/settings/keys" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">github.com/settings/keys</a> &rarr; <strong>New SSH key</strong> &rarr; paste &rarr; Save.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1">Step 4 &mdash; Test</p>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 overflow-x-auto">
              <span>ssh -T git@github.com</span>
              <button class="copy-btn px-3 py-1 bg-red-50 hover:bg-red-100 text-red-700 rounded text-xs font-semibold ml-4 font-sans" data-copy="ssh -T git@github.com">Copy</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Code Server -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Code Server (VS Code in Browser)</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Browser-based IDE with full project access:</p>
        <a href="https://dev.spiritmediapublishing.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-red-50 border border-stone-200 hover:bg-white hover:border-red-700 text-red-700 text-sm font-semibold rounded transition-colors">
          Open Code Server
        </a>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mt-3">Requires Tailscale VPN access.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- GitHub Organization -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">GitHub Organization</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-2">All repos are under the <a href="https://github.com/Spirit-Media-US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Spirit-Media-US</a> organization.</p>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm">Each client site has its own repo. The repo slug matches the directory name under <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/Sites/</code>.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Google Analytics -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Google Analytics</h2>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-stone-100 px-4 py-2 rounded">
            <div>
              <p class="text-stone-700 font-semibold">Google Tag Manager ID</p>
              <code class="text-xs text-stone-500">526725965</code>
            </div>
            <button class="copy-btn px-3 py-1 bg-red-50 hover:bg-opacity-30 text-red-700 rounded text-xs font-600" data-copy="526725965">Copy</button>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-stone-100 px-4 py-2 rounded">
            <div>
              <p class="text-stone-700 font-semibold">GA4 Property ID</p>
              <code class="text-xs text-stone-500">G-W3R21TNHTX</code>
            </div>
            <button class="copy-btn px-3 py-1 bg-red-50 hover:bg-opacity-30 text-red-700 rounded text-xs font-600" data-copy="G-W3R21TNHTX">Copy</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Rules -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Rules</h2>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">Always start in the site directory</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm"><code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">cd ~/Sites/&lt;slug&gt; && claude</code> &mdash; running Claude from <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/</code> or <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/Sites/</code> is blocked by a hook.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">All work goes to dev</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Never push to main. Only admin merges to main.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">Media never goes in Git</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Images &rarr; Sanity. Audio &rarr; R2. Video &rarr; YouTube iframe.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">MailtoLink required</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Every site uses a <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">MailtoLink</code> component. Bare <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">mailto:</code> links are banned.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">CSP headers required</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Every site needs <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">netlify.toml</code> with <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">Content-Security-Policy</code> headers.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">Sanity tokens are project-scoped</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Each Sanity project needs its own write token. Do not share tokens across projects.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Quick Start -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Quick Start Checklist</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700">
          <li>&check; Get your Bethel username from admin</li>
          <li>&check; Set up <a href="/onboarding" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Tailscale VPN</a></li>
          <li>&check; SSH into Bethel: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">ssh bethel</code></li>
          <li>&check; Set up your GitHub SSH key (see above)</li>
          <li>&check; Read the <a href="/playbook" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Playbook</a> for protocols</li>
          <li>&check; Read the <a href="/onboarding" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Onboarding</a> page for Claude setup</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Need Help -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Need Help?</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600">
          Check the <a href="/playbook" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Playbook</a> for protocols and workflows, or message the admin on Slack.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.copy-btn').forEach((btn) => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
        const text = this.getAttribute('data-copy');
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
          const originalText = this.textContent;
          this.textContent = 'Copied!';
          setTimeout(() => {
            this.textContent = originalText;
          }, 2000);
        });
      });
    });
  </script>
</PortalLayout>
